gujarati.context:
Farī Hari āvyā vartāla, tyāñthī gya jetalpur lāl;
Tiāñthī pachī sathaavyā śhyām, āvyā krpaḷu kajjisña gām.

Fari Hare came dwelling, from there went Lal Jetalpur;
From there after became peaceful Shyam, came merciful Krijisan village.

Renisame Avya Bhagavan, Deedaan Dase Ne Darshan Dan;
Dei Darshan Ne Vat Kari, Saakaar Roop Samjaava Hari.

Becomes:

"Darkness came from God, showed the vision to the devotee as a gift; 
Shed light on the vision and make me understand the true form of God."

Here is the translation:

People went to their home and lived, then called a sage; 
Cruel house does not accept people, then fate came and destroyed it.

Here is the translation:

Runners run running, ocean's roaring loudly, sweat droplets shine brightly on the body; 
Came to sit, having arrived at the threshold, looked and didn't see, did not get happy.
